{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/c-plus-plus/isascii-check-if-the-string-has-a-special-characters/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Labidi Aymen"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0db59b75-3f82-545d-a222-8eeed17bacde","excerpt":"When using C++ to serve multi-languages users, we need to validate the caractères in the string to find out what to do. In our case, we need to find out if…","html":"<p>When using C++ to serve <strong>multi-languages</strong> users, we need to validate the caractères in the string to find out what to do.</p>\n<p>In our case, we need to find out if there's a special character in the string to convert them,  and this was made by checking the decimal code of each character and check if it is above 127 or not,</p>\n<p>why <strong>127</strong>?</p>\n<p>Because the <strong>ASCII</strong> table told us that the characters code starts from 0 (NULL) and ends at 127(DEL)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://aymen.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/asciifull.gif\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<p>So we made this function.</p>\n<p>bool isASCII(const std::string&#x26; s)\n{\nreturn !std::any_of(s.begin(), s.end(), [](char c) {\nreturn static_cast<unsigned char>(c) > 127;\n});\n}</p>\n<p>And this how we used it</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>#include <iostream>\n#include <string>\n#include <algorithm></p>\n<p>bool isASCII(const std::string&#x26; s)\n{\nreturn !std::any_of(s.begin(), s.end(), [](char c) {\nreturn static_cast<unsigned char>(c) > 127;\n});\n}</p>\n<p>int main(){\nstd::string testString = \"not a valid Ãscii\";\nstd::cout &#x3C;&#x3C; \"Is valid ASCII \" &#x3C;&#x3C; isASCII(testString.c_str()) &#x3C;&#x3C; std::endl;\n}</p>\n<p>And the output will be:</p>\n<p>Is valid ASCII 0</p>\n<p>0 as NULL is C++</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>PS: Will share snippets as I'm learning C++</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"(C++) isASCII(string) : Check if the string has a special characters","date":"March 02, 2020","description":null,"categories":["c-plus-plus"],"cove